# RoofController API Test Requests
# Use VS Code REST Client extension to execute these requests

# To test:
# 1. Press Ctrl+Shift+P (Cmd+Shift+P on Mac)
# 2. Type "Tasks: Run Task" and select it
# 3. Choose "watch" to start the API
# 4. Wait for the application to start
# 5. Use the requests below to test the API

### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5195
@contentType = application/json

### Get current roof status
# Returns the current state of the roof controller
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/v4/RoofControl/Status
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Open the roof
# Starts opening the roof
# Monitor Status endpoint to track progress
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v4/RoofControl/Open
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Close the roof
# Starts closing the roof
# Monitor Status endpoint to track progress
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v4/RoofControl/Close
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Stop roof movement
# Immediately stops any roof movement
# Use in emergency situations or when movement needs to be halted
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/v4/RoofControl/Stop
Accept: {{contentType}}

### Response Schemas:

# Status Response:
# {
#   "status": "Open" | "Closed" | "Opening" | "Closing" | "Stopped" | "NotInitialized"
# }

# Initialize Response:
# {
#   "initialized": true
# }

### Error Responses:
# 400 Bad Request - Invalid operation or state
# 500 Internal Server Error - Hardware or system error
# 503 Service Unavailable - Controller not initialized

### Usage Notes:
# 1. Always call Initialize before other operations
# 2. Poll Status endpoint to monitor roof movement
# 3. Stop can be called at any time during movement
# 4. Operations will fail if controller is disposed
